; CCON audit B2 - doresize() does nothing on GROW, so an enlarged
; window extends downward over scrollback ring rows it has already
; recycled
;
; Run:    Execute S:ccon-b2
; Then:   drag the window's bottom-right corner to make it TALLER
;         (more rows - width doesn't matter)
; Then:   look at the NEW rows exposed at the bottom
;
;   BROKEN -> the new rows show old numbers out of order, or repeats
;             of numbers already visible further up
;   FIXED  -> the new rows continue the numbered sequence in order,
;             or are blank once you have grown past all 60 of them
;
; 60 rows is deliberately more than any CCON window used in testing
; holds at once, so the ring is guaranteed to hold more history than
; one screen - the precondition doresize()'s grow block needs.
;
; No undo script needed: NewShell CCON: (or close/reopen the window)
; clears it.
Type S:ccon-b2-fill
